p: Genes differentially expressed by 6-h DCVC treatment were also enriched in pathways, as identified by GSEA. Although 6 h DCVC treatment yielded no pathways that were upregulated with 10 µM DCVC, two pathways were downregulated (Fig. 3e). Treatment with 20 µM DCVC upregulated one pathway and downregulated six pathways (Fig. 3f). Of the six downregulated pathways, four were involved in embryonic development, the most common category. Representative pathways in this category include epithelial-mesenchymal transition (NES = − 1.97, FDR = 0.001) and myogenesis (NES = − 1.79, FDR = 0.004). Other categories represented among downregulated pathways included immune response (2) proliferation (1) and cellular organization (1). The overall pattern of pathways affected by DCVC treatment for 6 h consisted primarily of the downregulation of pathways associated with embryonic development.
